definitions.definition: Under normal conditions or circumstances ; usually ; most of the time
examples: Normally , I eat breakfast at 6am, but today, I got up late and didn't eat until 9.

definitions.definition: In the expected or customary manner .
examples: Lisa ate normally , until she realised that she was late for choir , when she sped up.

definitions.definition: To a usual or customary extent or degree.
examples: He was abnormally agitated, she only normally so.

definitions.definition: In the manner of a variable with a Gaussian distribution.

main_definition: Under normal conditions or circumstances ; usually ; most of the time
secondary_definitions: In the expected or customary manner .
To a usual or customary extent or degree.
( mathematics , statistics ) In the manner of a variable with a Gaussian distribution.
